# !!! PLACEHOLDER — US-017 audit-trail stub !!!
#
# This file is a committed audit-trail copy of the PaneFlow release
# signing key's PUBLIC half. It does NOT contain real key material yet.
#
# The real key must be generated by the project operator following the
# procedure in docs/release-signing.md §1, then this file is OVERWRITTEN
# with the ASCII-armored public key emitted by:
#
#     gpg --armor --export "$FPR" > packaging/paneflow-release.asc
#
# Until that happens, this file exists only to satisfy US-017's AC2
# contract ("public key ASCII-armored, committed as
# packaging/paneflow-release.asc for audit trail") as a bootstrap stub.
#
# Importantly, neither `release.yml` nor `repo-publish.yml` READS this
# file. They both operate from the imported GPG_PRIVATE_KEY secret. So
# this stub does NOT block CI signing from working once the secret is
# populated; the stub is purely for human audit.
#
# Deliberately NOT wrapped in `-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----` /
# `-----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----` markers — gpg-armor parsers
# would fail on the comment-only content. When the real key is pasted
# in, the armor markers arrive with it (they are part of the
# `gpg --armor --export` output).
#
# After the real key is committed here, consumers can verify signatures:
#
#     gpg --import packaging/paneflow-release.asc
#     dpkg-sig --verify paneflow-*.deb
#     rpm --import packaging/paneflow-release.asc
#     rpm --checksig -v paneflow-*.rpm
